This paper proposes a new wireless resource allocation strategy for LoRaWAN, which is a network infrastructure for IoT devices. The paper focuses on improving the network capacity by assigning spreading factors to end-devices. This topic falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers channel capture, which is a characteristic of wireless communication systems, and this could be relevant to the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed strategy in different operating/load conditions and network topology configurations, which could be related to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
